{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 190°C. Line a deep sided baking tray (25 x 35 cm) with baking paper, allowing a 2.5cm overhang, and set aside.","Place hazelnuts into mixing bowl and mill <b>5 sec\/speed 8<b>, until finely chopped. Transfer into a bowl and set aside. Thoroughly clean and dry mixing bowl."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg whites and cream of tartar into mixing bowl and whip <b>2 min\/speed 3<b> <strong>,<\/strong> <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong> <strong>,<\/strong> or until soft peaks form.","Mix <b>3 min\/speed 3<b>, slowly adding sugar through hole in mixing bowl lid 1 teaspoon at a time until combined. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>.","Add vanilla and reserved hazelnuts and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 3<b>. Transfer into prepared baking tray, ensuring mixture is spread evenly and there are no air pockets. Bake for 20 minutes (190°C).","Carefully flip over onto a piece of baking paper slightly larger than the roulade. Gently peel away the paper from the roulade. Clean and dry mixing bowl and butterfly whisk."," <strong>Re-insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream into mixing bowl and whip <b>until soft peaks form\/speed 3<b>, watching carefully through hole in mixing bowl lid to avoid over whipping.","Spread whipped cream mixture evenly over cooled roulade, leaving a 1 cm border around the edge. Space mandarin segments evenly on top of cream. Using long edge of the roulade, carefully roll into a tight log shape using the baking paper to assist in rolling. Remove paper. Place roulade seam side down onto a serving platter. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place chocolate into mixing bowl and melt <b>2 min\/50°C\/speed 3<b>. Drizzle roulade with melted chocolate. Place into refrigerator to chill for approx. 30 minutes. Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before slicing and serving. "]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g hazelnuts, roasted and skin removed","4 egg whites","1 pinch cream of tartar","200 g caster sugar","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","300 g pouring (whipping) cream","310 g tinned mandarin segments, drained","60 g dark chocolate (gluten free), broken into pieces"]}],"id":"r114669","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-5XpB-YXk3og\/XZWfl4Idr_I\/AAAAAAAAfHA\/Tt5DeWwFH9c-V42seYJMKlwiVukimulqwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_yQoeTITV5nx2npe1.png","title":"Hazelnut meringue roulade","publishedAt":"2016-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7.5 g","fat":"32.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"45.1 g","calories":"2090 kJ \/ 497 kcal"},"usefulItems":"deep-sided baking tray, baking paper, bowl, serving platter, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["You can replace tinned mandarin segments with drained tinned fruit of choice or fresh strawberries."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 30m","6 portions"]}